{"id":538,"date":"2021-04-09T16:02:00","date_gmt":"2021-04-09T16:02:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/programming.sdarobotics.org\/?page_id=538"},"modified":"2021-04-09T16:31:04","modified_gmt":"2021-04-09T16:31:04","slug":"programming-the-arduino","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/programming-the-arduino\/","title":{"rendered":"Programming the Arduino"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Before we build the Arduino board, we are going to want to program the Arduino. For this you must install the Arduino IDE which can be found&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.arduino.cc\/en\/Main\/Software\" target=\"_blank\">here<\/a>. After you have install the software you are going to need to download the needed libraries which are included in the&nbsp;<strong>Robot Tools<\/strong>&nbsp;download which&nbsp;can be found&nbsp;<a href=\"\/downloads\/robottools2021.zip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here<\/a>. If you haven\u2019t done so already, unzip the file onto your desktop. If you open the&nbsp;<strong>RobotTools2021<\/strong>&nbsp;folder you will find a sub-folder named&nbsp;<strong>Arduino<\/strong>&nbsp;which you need to set up as your Sketchbook location. To do this, choose the&nbsp;<strong>Preferences&nbsp;<\/strong>option from the&nbsp;<strong>File<\/strong>&nbsp;menu:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"500\" height=\"431\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoSetup.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-542\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoSetup.jpg 500w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoSetup-300x259.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Which should bring up the following dialog:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoPref.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoPref.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-545\" width=\"599\" height=\"501\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoPref.jpg 726w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoPref-300x251.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Set the&nbsp;<strong>Sketchbook location<\/strong>&nbsp;field to point to the location of the&nbsp;<strong>Arduino<\/strong>&nbsp;sub-folder that you placed on your desktop.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Close and restart your&nbsp;<strong>Arduino<\/strong>&nbsp;program. Now open the&nbsp;<strong>Arduino<\/strong>&nbsp;project named&nbsp;<strong>PiRobotDual<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PiRobotDual.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PiRobotDual.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-548\" width=\"620\" height=\"429\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PiRobotDual.jpg 742w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PiRobotDual-300x208.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Which should open the following sketch:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"574\" height=\"654\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoProject.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-551\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoProject.jpg 574w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoProject-263x300.jpg 263w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 574px) 100vw, 574px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now connect your Arduino to your computer using a USB cable. After the drivers have been installed (which may take a while), you should be able to select the&nbsp;<strong>COM<\/strong>&nbsp;port for your device from the&nbsp;<strong>Tools<\/strong>&nbsp;menu. Also make sure that the <strong>Arduino Nano<\/strong> is selected. You may also need to select the <strong>Old Bootloader<\/strong> option as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"571\" height=\"651\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SelectPort.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-552\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SelectPort.jpg 571w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SelectPort-263x300.jpg 263w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 571px) 100vw, 571px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now click the little right arrow button in the upper left to compile and download the program to your Arduino. Once it has been downloaded, open a&nbsp;<strong>Serial Monitor<\/strong>&nbsp;window by clicking on the little magnifying glass in the upper right corner:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"476\" height=\"470\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoStartMonitor.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-556\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoStartMonitor.jpg 476w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoStartMonitor-300x296.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 476px) 100vw, 476px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>When the window is open make sure that the&nbsp;<strong>baud<\/strong>&nbsp;rate in the lower right corner is showing&nbsp;<strong>115200 baud<\/strong>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoConsole.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoConsole.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-557\" width=\"641\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoConsole.jpg 887w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoConsole-300x151.jpg 300w, http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/ArduinoConsole-768x386.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 641px) 100vw, 641px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>If the window now looks like the one above, you have successfully programmed your Arduino. Disconnect it from your computer and it is ready to go.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Before we build the Arduino board, we are going to want to program the Arduino. For this you must install the Arduino IDE which can be found&nbsp;here. After you have install the software you are going to need to download the needed libraries which are included in the&nbsp;Robot Tools&nbsp;download which&nbsp;can be found&nbsp;here. If you haven\u2019t&hellip;&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/programming-the-arduino\/\" class=\"\" rel=\"bookmark\">Read More &raquo;<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Programming the Arduino<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","template":"","meta":{"neve_meta_sidebar":"","neve_meta_container":"","neve_meta_enable_content_width":"","neve_meta_content_width":0,"neve_meta_title_alignment":"","neve_meta_author_avatar":"","neve_post_elements_order":"","neve_meta_disable_header":"","neve_meta_disable_footer":"","neve_meta_disable_title":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/538"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/programming.team2102.org\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users